
[1]softly

   SOFT'LY, adv.

   1. Without hardness.

   2. Not with force or violence; gently; as, be softly pressed my hand.

   3. Not loudly; without noise; as, speak softly; walk softly. In this
   dark silence softly leave the town.

   4. Gently; placidly. She softly lays him on a flowery bed.

   5. Mildly; tenderly. The king must die; though pity softly pleads
   within my soul.
